<paragraph id="F1589726FF8CFFB7CED0FF12FEACFE9F" blockId="4.[151,1437,236,780]" box="[151,263,236,265]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis id="C3934B34FF8CFFB7CED0FF12FEACFE9F" box="[151,263,236,265]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F1589726FF8CFFB7CE97FEEFFCBFFC9A" blockId="4.[151,1437,236,780]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">
Until now five 
<taxonomicName id="36E7ECA5FF8CFFB7CFD5FEEFFE4CFEBB" authorityName="Keifer" authorityYear="1944" box="[402,487,273,301]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3934B34FF8CFFB7CFD5FEEFFE4CFEBB" box="[402,487,273,301]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Aceria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species have been recorded on 
<taxonomicName id="36E7ECA5FF8CFFB7CD3DFEECFC7DFEB8" authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[890,982,273,302]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis id="C3934B34FF8CFFB7CD3DFEECFC7DFEB8" box="[890,982,273,302]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">P. alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation id="BC65A29DFF8CFFB7CDA0FEEFFBE3FEB8" box="[999,1096,273,302]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="4.[151,216,854,878]" captionText="Table 1. Aceria mite species collected on Populus alba L. worldwide and their type host, alternative hosts and habitus (according to Amrine and de Lillo, unpublished database)." pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Table 1</tableCitation>
). Apart 
<taxonomicName id="36E7ECA5FF8CFFB7CAF3FEEFFACDFEB8" baseAuthorityName="Keifer" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[1204,1382,273,302]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parapopuli">
<emphasis id="C3934B34FF8CFFB7CAF3FEEFFACDFEB8" box="[1204,1382,273,302]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">A. parapopuli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the descriptions of the other species appear to be not consistent with the current descriptive standard (
<bibRefCitation id="9576EAD7FF8CFFB7CB3AFEC8FED3FEEE" author="de Lillo, E. &amp; Craemer, C. &amp; Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Nuzzaci, G." pageId="4" pageNumber="133" pagination="283 - 307" refId="ref5047" refString="de Lillo, E., Craemer, C., Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Nuzzaci, G. (2010) Recommended procedures and techniques for morphological studies of Eriophyoidea (Acari: Prostigmata). Experimental and Applied Acarology, 51 (1 - 3): 283 - 307." type="journal article" year="2010">
de Lillo 
<emphasis id="C3934B34FF8CFFB7CEA5FEA5FE8DFEE1" box="[226,294,346,375]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
). The prodorsal shield ornamentation of Iranian specimens is closer to 
<taxonomicName id="36E7ECA5FF8CFFB7CB76FEA5FA37FEE1" baseAuthorityName="Nalepa" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1329,1436,347,375]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varia">
<emphasis id="C3934B34FF8CFFB7CB76FEA5FA37FEE1" box="[1329,1436,347,375]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">A. varia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to the drawing by 
<bibRefCitation id="9576EAD7FF8CFFB7CC55FE81FD66FE0A" author="Nalepa A." box="[530,717,383,412]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" pagination="525 - 540" refId="ref5551" refString="Nalepa A. (1892) Neue Arten der Gattung Phytoptus Duj. und Cecidophyes Nal. Denkschriften kaiser Akademie der Wissenschaften: Mathematisch-Naturwissenschaftliche, Wien, 59: 525 - 540 + 4 pls." type="book chapter" year="1892">Nalepa (1892)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="9576EAD7FF8CFFB7CD57FE81FC7FFE0A" author="Boczek, J." box="[784,980,383,412]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" pagination="393 - 398" refId="ref4873" refString="Boczek, J. (1969) Studies on mites (Acarina) living on plants in Poland. XI. Bulletin of the Polish Academy of Sciences Cl. 5, 17 (6): 393 - 398." type="journal article" year="1969">Boczek (1969)</bibRefCitation>
. The main differences between the Iranian specimens and 
<bibRefCitation id="9576EAD7FF8CFFB7CF84FE5AFD25FE57" author="Nalepa A." box="[451,654,420,449]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" pagination="525 - 540" refId="ref5551" refString="Nalepa A. (1892) Neue Arten der Gattung Phytoptus Duj. und Cecidophyes Nal. Denkschriften kaiser Akademie der Wissenschaften: Mathematisch-Naturwissenschaftliche, Wien, 59: 525 - 540 + 4 pls." type="book chapter" year="1892">Nalepa's (1892)</bibRefCitation>
description regards the shape of the frontal lobe (evident in the Iranian specimens and neglected in the given descriptions, but the previous authors might have not seen the lobe due to the less sharpening of the available instruments) and the length of setae 
<emphasis id="C3934B34FF8CFFB7CB26FE11FAC4FD9D" box="[1377,1391,495,523]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">e</emphasis>
(as long as setae 
<emphasis id="C3934B34FF8CFFB7CF04FDECFEF8FDB9" box="[323,339,530,559]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">d</emphasis>
in the original description but in the Iranian specimens setae 
<emphasis id="C3934B34FF8CFFB7CA2FFDECFBD3FDB9" box="[1128,1144,530,559]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">d</emphasis>
is longer (46–60) than setae 
<emphasis id="C3934B34FF8CFFB7CEA6FDC6FF44FDC2" box="[225,239,568,596]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">e</emphasis>
(15–17)). Iranian specimens have been found vagrants on the 
<taxonomicName id="36E7ECA5FF8CFFB7CA5CFDC6FBD2FDC2" authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1051,1145,567,596]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis id="C3934B34FF8CFFB7CA5CFDC6FBD2FDC2" box="[1051,1145,567,596]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">P. alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
leaves, while 
<taxonomicName id="36E7ECA5FF8CFFB7CB73FDC6FA36FDC2" baseAuthorityName="Nalepa" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1332,1437,568,596]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varia">
<emphasis id="C3934B34FF8CFFB7CB73FDC6FA36FDC2" box="[1332,1437,568,596]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">A. varia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
causes erinea on the undersurface of the leaves and bulges on the opposite side of the lamina on 
<taxonomicName id="36E7ECA5FF8CFFB7CBC6FDA3FF50FD08" authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tremula">
<emphasis id="C3934B34FF8CFFB7CBC6FDA3FF50FD08" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">P. tremula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to 
<bibRefCitation id="9576EAD7FF8CFFB7CFEAFD7FFDC4FD08" author="Boczek, J." box="[429,623,641,670]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" pagination="393 - 398" refId="ref4873" refString="Boczek, J. (1969) Studies on mites (Acarina) living on plants in Poland. XI. Bulletin of the Polish Academy of Sciences Cl. 5, 17 (6): 393 - 398." type="journal article" year="1969">Boczek (1969)</bibRefCitation>
, whereas it is related to felty silver surface on the underside of the leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="36E7ECA5FF8CFFB7CF04FD59FE0AFD55" authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[323,417,678,707]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis id="C3934B34FF8CFFB7CF04FD59FE0AFD55" box="[323,417,678,707]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">P. alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="89F0D7B6FF8CFFB7CF8CFD58FD8FFD55" box="[459,548,678,707]" name="Poland" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Poland</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9576EAD7FF8CFFB7CC72FD58FD67FD55" author="Szulc, W." box="[565,716,678,707]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" pagination="27 - 55" refId="ref5697" refString="Szulc, W. (1966) Szpeciele (Eriophyidae) z wyzyny Lodzkiej. [Gall mites (Eriophyidae) of Lodz Upland]. Zeszyty naukowe Uniwersytetu Lodzkiego Seria II, 21: 27 - 55." type="journal article" year="1966">Szulc 1966</bibRefCitation>
). Therefore, in absence of further data and with the will to be quite conservative, the Iranian specimens were redescribed as 
<taxonomicName id="36E7ECA5FF8CFFB7CDABFD35FBFAFD71" baseAuthorityName="Nalepa" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1004,1105,715,743]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varia">
<emphasis id="C3934B34FF8CFFB7CDABFD35FBFAFD71" box="[1004,1105,715,743]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">A. varia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to the observed similarities with the previously described species.
</paragraph>
